Social Security, medicare, medicaid, and high interest on debt is up. That's to be expected. Our people are older and are collecting more benefits. And we're paying more interest on more debt. Trump hasn't touched those things yet. It's just the natural progression of things.


It does show what Trump has done to decrease spending has been a success: DOE expenses are down, so is TSA and USAID.


The article also explains that while DOGE has done somethings - namely all the fed gov worker cuts - we haven't seen the effects of that yet since they're still on payroll, severance payouts etc.
